## 2. Structural & Layout Breakdown

The paper was programmatically generated using `python-docx` with direct XML-level section column controls to ensure formatting compliance:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Title Section: Single Column] --> B[Continuous Section Break]
    B --> C[Body Section: Two Columns]
    C --> D[Abstract & Index Terms]
    C --> E[1. Introduction]
    C --> F[2. Methodology]
    C --> G[3. Results and Analysis]
    C --> H[4. Discussion]
    C --> I[5. Conclusion]
    C --> J[6. References]
```

### Applied Formatting Parameters
1. **Title**: Bold,Centered, All-caps, 14pt Times New Roman, positioned exactly **1.38"** from the top page edge.
2. **Body Section Margins**: Top: **1.0"**, Bottom: **1.0"**, Left: **0.75"**, Right: **0.75"**.
3. **Columns**: **2 columns** with **0.24"** gap spacing.
4. **Paragraph Spacing**: Strict single spacing with **6pt spacing after** paragraphs. No indent on the first paragraph of a subsection, **0.25" indent** on subsequent paragraphs.
5. **Headings**: Centered, Bold, uppercase, numbered (e.g. `1. INTRODUCTION`).
6. **Subheadings**: Bold, left-aligned, Title Case, numbered (e.g. `2.1. Study Area`).
7. **References**: Sequential square brackets numbering (e.g. `[1]`, `[2]`).

